# Walkthrough: Chat History Persistence Fix

I have implemented server-side chat history persistence for the Gemini DevTool Suite. This ensures that your chat history is saved to a local file and persists across browser restarts and cache clears.

## Changes Made

### backend
- **[server.js](file:///c:/Users/shoaib/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/gemini-devtool-suite/server.js)**: Added `/api/history` GET and POST endpoints to manage `chat_history.json`.

### frontend
- **[ChatInterface.tsx](file:///c:/Users/shoaib/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/gemini-devtool-suite/components/ChatInterface.tsx)**: Updated the component to fetch history from the server on load and save it whenever new messages are sent.

## Verification Results

### Automated API Test
I created and ran a test script [test_history_api.js](file:///c:/Users/shoaib/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/gemini-devtool-suite/test_history_api.js) which confirmed that the history is correctly read from and written to the server.

```bash
node test_history_api.js
--- Testing History API ---
Initial History: []
POST Result: { success: true }
Updated History: [ { role: 'user', text: 'Hello Test', timestamp: ... } ]
SUCCESS: History persisted correctly!
```

### File Verification
The chat history is now saved in `chat_history.json` in your project root.

## How to use
1. Make sure your backend server is running: `node server.js`
2. Run your frontend: `npm run dev`
3. Your chat history will now automatically save and load from `chat_history.json`.
